	import java.io.BufferedReader;
	import java.io.IOException;
	import java.io.InputStreamReader;
	import java.math.BigInteger;
	
	
	public class Main {
		public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException 
		{
			BufferedReader buf = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(System.in));
			String line = buf.readLine();
			String[] tokens = line.split(" ");
			BigInteger a = BigInteger.valueOf(Long.parseLong(tokens[0]));
			BigInteger b = BigInteger.valueOf(Long.parseLong(tokens[1]));
			BigInteger g,temp=null;
			BigInteger one = BigInteger.valueOf(1);
			BigInteger minusone = BigInteger.valueOf(-1);
			while(!(a.equals(one) && b.equals(one)))
			{
				g = a.gcd(b);	
				a = a.divide(g);
				b = b.divide(g);
				while(!a.equals(one))
				{
					
					temp = (b.divide(a)).add(one);
					System.out.print(temp + " ");
					a = b.multiply(minusone).mod(a).add(a).mod(a);
					b = b.multiply(temp);
					g = a.gcd(b);	
					a = a.divide(g);
					b = b.divide(g);
				}
				System.out.print(b + "\n");
				line = buf.readLine();
				tokens = line.split(" ");
				a = BigInteger.valueOf(Long.parseLong(tokens[0]));
				b = BigInteger.valueOf(Long.parseLong(tokens[1]));
				
			}
		}
	}
